-- Terra Firma May Float Infinis Energy Arm, Sunday Telegraph Says
-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 2012-05-27T14:58:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-27/terra-firma-may-float-infinis-energy-unit-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Terra Firma Capital Partners Ltd. is
planning to float its Infinis Plc energy unit in a stock listing
that may be worth 1 billion pounds ($1.6 billion),  The Sunday
Telegraph  said, citing people close to the company that it
didn’t identify.  Terra Firma is trying to raise money for a new fund and
will probably begin the Infinis sales process in early 2013, the
newspaper reported.  Terra Firma and Infinis didn’t return phone calls seeking
comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
